加價<br />\n就算黨鐵個可加可減都要入議會討論過先可以准許加價<br />\n今次依個同趁火打劫冇分別"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-02-22T02:24:31.000Z","msg":"而係作為公共業務點解可以自由加價?<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nElectricity deregulation in Texas, approved by Texas Senate Bill 7 on January 1, 2002, called for the creation of the Electric Utility Restructuring Legislative Oversight Committee to oversee implementation of the bill.[disputed &ndash; discuss] According to the law, deregulation would be phased in over several years.<br />\n<br />\nAs a result, 85%[1] of Texas power consumers (those served by a company not owned by a municipality or a utility cooperative) could choose their electricity service from a variety of retail electric providers (REPs), including the incumbent utility. The incumbent utility in the area still owns and maintains the local power lines (and is the company to call in the event of a power outage) and was not subject to deregulation. Customers served by cooperatives or municipal utilities could choose an alternate REP only if the utility has opted in to deregulation; to date,[when?] only the area served by the Nueces Electric Cooperative has chosen to opt in"},{"pid":"d410c6bd56fac7cbb7b918b4f56b5bb1e08a1c86","tid":2417412,"uid":33213,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"a6a918b641985fad44ce6c76c55c65e02cb7bca5","tid":2417412,"uid":66324,"like":1,"dislike":1,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-02-22T01:00:51.000Z","msg":"搬黎左膠大州染紅佢<br />\n熱撚到溶左"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-02-22T02:31:26.000Z","msg":"咁樣應該係德州染藍先<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"990aa0e826a58112aaf22ca2194a2c5816bc0ec6","tid":2417412,"uid":303977,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-02-22T02:34:54.000Z","msg":"樓豬凍撚死未<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hk